Scientific presentation:
1) determine the needs of your customers:
	- how much do they know about your topic, and what is their level of technical sophistication?
2) make it:
	- select your core question or hypothesis
	- surround it with a logical flow of data and clearly defined sub-question
	- you need something to contain that hypothesis and supporting data
3) finally, you must design attrative visual aids and respond well to questions

purpose:
- inform, persuade, inspire or teach ?

use sans serif for presentations

black on yellow is the fastest for reading
think of daltonians

no red or orange backgounds! or only a one time thing to wake up the audience

items in diagonal to imply time flow:

	| item one blabla |

			| item two blabla |

					| item three blabla |